article.headline: San Diego St. 62, Fresno St. 58
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. -- Billy White scored 22 points, including the go-ahead free throws with 19.5 seconds remaining, as San Diego State held off Fresno State 62-58 on Monday night in the West Coast Classic. Tyrone Shelley added 17 points for the Aztecs (3-1), capped by two free throws with 2.9 seconds left that clinched the victory. Greg Smith led the Bulldogs (2-2) with 16 points and 10 rebounds. Mike Ladd added 14 points. Neither team led by more than four points in a hotly contested second half. Before his go-ahead free throws, White tied the score 56-56 by sneaking behind Fresno State's zone for a putback following a missed 3-pointer with 1:59 left. The Bulldogs led 29-25 at halftime thanks in large part to Ladd's hot shooting. Ladd scored 11 of the Bulldogs' first 16 points, including three 3-pointers.
